raspberrypi code for a seesaw: tilt-switch pair, and adafruit LSM9DS0

Call the ends 'a' and 'b'.

When 'a' is down, play a sound, $HOME/fun/seesawsound2.wav.
When 'b' is down, play the other sound, .../seesawsound.wav.


Startup was /etc/rc.local +
(cd ~pi/fun && ./driver.py ) 2>&1 | logger -t seesaw&

